President, FIBA Africa Zone 3, Col. Sam Amedu (retd.), has charged the country’s representatives at the inaugural Basketball  Africa League, Rivers Hoopers, to do Nigeria proud by winning the competition. The inaugural edition of BAL tips off in Kigali, Rwanda May 16, with Hoopers one of the 12 clubs in action. While on a visit to the Port Harcourt-base side, Ahmedu urged Nigerians to support the team. “We need to encourage Hoopers to do well. As our flag bearers, they deserve all the support to attain success,” Ahmedu said. The Dodan Warriors proprietor also presented the team with match balls, T-shirts and N50,000 to the team. Camped at the indoor hall of the Teslim Balogun Stadium, Lagos, the Hoopers are expected to leave for Kigali May 14. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com